<@U0ESBF4AV> about your optional library I tried that and it has quite a few shortcomings. First of all you need to implement parcelable, to do that you need to store the class type T of `Optional<T>`. Secondly, keep in mind that AutoValue has Java 8 and Guava Optional integration, so if you want to support that your package name will need to be the exact same. Third if users use Optional a lot they alocate an extra object per value, how bad this is is not clear since no one has really benchmarked it

attachments.title: The Wonderful World of Keyboards
attachments.text: With the beta release of Atom 1.12, we’re rolling out some long-awaited improvements to Atom’s support for international keyboard layouts. Before 1.12, users on many layouts needed to install a community-maintained package called keyboard-localization to enable full support for their keyboards, but now users from all locales should experience hassle free keyboarding in Atom’s default configuration. In this post, we’ll discuss the challenges we faced recognizing keybindings and how we arrived at a solution.
